Up )

do { \
uint64_t w = reverse ? ~*pos : *pos; \
\
if (Low) w &= BITMASK_GE(uint64_t, Low); \
if (Up != 64) w &= BITMASK_LT(uint64_t, Up); \
\
if (w) { \
return len + bsr64(w) - (Up); \
} \
len -= (Up) - (Low); \
pos--; \
} while (0)

Function Documentation

◆ bsf()

ssize_t bsf ( const void * data,
size_t start_bit,
size_t len,
bool reverse )

Find the first bit at 1 or 0 in a sequence of bits.

Parameters
[in]datathe memory to scan
[in]start_bitoffset of the first bit after data
[in]lenmaximum number of bits to scan after start_bit
[in]reverseif reverse, look for the first 0 instead of the first 1
Returns
-1 if no 1 (or 0 if reverse was set) was found, else the offset of the first bit of the given value relative to start_bit.

◆ bsr()

ssize_t bsr ( const void * data,
size_t start_bit,
size_t len,
bool reverse )

Find the last bit at 1 or 0 in a sequence of bits.

Same as bsf but scan from the end of the stream (bitwise).

See also
bsf.
